The**Check Email Status Condition**in a Smart Flow enables you to create different paths or trigger actions based on the response to an email sent to a contact.**Topics Covered:***   [How to Configure Check Email Status Condition](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780742415769-Check-Email-Status#h_01J8KVHK1DD4KFK8F8236DKN2D)

*   [Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780742415769-Check-Email-Status#h_01J8KWZT8NMJZVJ8QV0X8CWQYY)


### How to Configure Check Email Status Condition


*   When setting up a Smart Flow, choose the**Check Email Status**Condition.

![](./Check Email Status – Salesmate_files/mceclip0.png)

After selecting, you'll need to configure the**Check Email Status**condition by providing the following details:


***Name:**Assign a clear and descriptive name for the condition.

***Description:**Provide a brief explanation of the condition’s purpose.

***Select Contact:**Choose the contact for whom the email status will be checked.

***Select Email:**Choose one of the following options,
    ***Email from flow:**Select an email directly used within the current flow.
    ***Email sent using a template:**Choose an email that was sent using a pre-designed template.
    ***Email sent using a campaign:**Select an email that was part of a larger email campaign.
    ***Email sent using a journey email:**Choose an email that was part of an automated journey or series.
    ***Email Event:**Choose the specific email event to track.

*   Once the configuration is completed, hit**Save**.

![](./Check Email Status – Salesmate_files/mceclip1.png)


### Practical Example

When sending an important invoice, you can set up a flow with the "Check Email Status" condition to monitor engagement. This allows you to automatically check if the email has been opened or clicked, ensuring timely follow-ups based on the contact's interaction with your message.
